"It just seems obvious to me that if you play your class to 50 and don't like where it ended up in the food chain. You try a different class. We all know it's not that hard. And the game truly is more fun at mid levels."<P><BR>This is complete bull****.  I highly doubt you have any characters above level 55. <P>"If all that you care about is end game, then I think you might be playing the wrong class. Balancing might not mean that every class becomes all powerful in the raid situation. You can't have your cake and eat it too. You can't be a Mage for 50 levels then become a wizard."<P>If Magician pets were scaled right post 50 and if pathing was not an issue we would not be having this discussion.<P>As for starting over playing another class.. it took 1 year for me to get to level 60+.  Not all of us have 40+ hours a week to devote to leveling.  I happen to enjoy the concept of the Magician so I stayed with it. <P>"I play 7 different classes. My wizard is most work of any of my characters to play. She takes the most strategy and has the smallest room for error. When you MAKE the wizard it even tells you it's difficult. I fully expect to do more damage than a character who leveled alot easier. I will have earned it."<P>So how many of your 7 characters are level 55+?<P>So you think you earned your levels more then a mage?  This is a big laugh... you can quad kite from mid 40s right to 60 and beyond.  A Mage needs to kill the mobs one by one.  A Mage does not have mana regen until level 58. <P>"You may not agree with me. You may not like what I say. I know you don't want to hear it. I didn't want to know my Beastlord was going to have it rough at the end either. But ANY pet class that has to deal damage is not going to be a shining star in end game."<P>I dunno about this.. necros kick some serious butt right to 60.  They don't need groups.  I know some necros that can solo the named mobs in The Grey and collect nice loot with little effort.<P>The way I see it VI/SoE will eventually loose the majority of their player base if they do not give each and every class a meaningful role in the high end game.  Its a matter of time.  All things end, even EQ and there are so many holes in EQ's "balance".  Games Like Warcraft Online and Shadowbane could take 20 percent of EQs player population each next year.<P>EQ will wither slowly because of the DAOC's and AO's of the world.<P>Part of the reason is that clas sbalance was never considered improtant by the kids that developed and set up the game.<P>--------------------<P>Rthen Majere<BR>Arch Mage<BR>Master of the Orb<BR>Baron of Fungus Grove
