I think the perception that crits are enabling wizards to do more damage is greater than the reality. I have notieced I am more welcome in groups now than before the crit patch but the reality is I score a crit maybe once every 2 hours or so and when I do it for like maybe 30 or 40 more damage than the spell usually does. I think they've made the FAR too rare to be of any real effect. Considering a warrior with a high dex will crit every other fight, sometimes hitting for double damage or more on a crippling blow the spell crits are pretty insignificant in an standard XP group. Not to mention a warrior has a pretty good chance of incresing his number of crits by raising his dex, I can do nothing (that I'm aware of) to increase my chance. If they made crits so they did 2x or 3x damage then I could understand their rarity, but when the damage increase is so little they should be FAR FAR more common than they are.<P>--------------------<P>Kevin V<BR>43 Paladin <BR>36 Bard<BR>31 Shaman<BR>45 Necromancer (Whirlwind of the Night) <BR>39 Wizard (Whirlwind of the Night) <BR>Rodchet Nife
