<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Maybe this can help show how the two classes are ballenced...<P>Mages - have pets / nuke backups<BR>Beastlord - have pets / heal & haste backups<BR>Necro - have pets / fear kiting<BR>Chanters - have pets ( charmed ) / CC & haste<BR>Wizards - have nukes...lots' and lot's of nukes<P>OF COURSE WIZARDS ARE GONNA BE THE BEST AT NUKING! IT'S WHAT THEY DO!!!<P>Magicians summon things. Can a wizard summon something? Sure, a lightsource, and familiars.<P>Magicians get 4 different types of pets, and the epic get's a 150 point PROC!!!<P>Let's touch on Magician DS's too...<BR>Now technically, druids get the highest DS in the game now ( at 34 dmg ) but up until then, MAGES did...<P>let's do some numbers.<BR>War has a 33 point DS on...he get's quadded once per second for a 6 min fight. He has defencive on, and CH'd so he don't die.<P>Now, here's the numbers. ( 33dmg * 60sec/min * 6min * 1 quad ( or 4 if you can't do the math ) = 47520dmg in 6 min...)<BR>All that done by some little pissant 30mana spell that a mage can do.<P>What about if you're tank light...<BR>would you rather have a TANK? or a blaster?<P>If you choose blaster, when you can have a TANK and BLASTER in 1, you're just dumb.<P>Granted, Wizzy's can turn mob's into crispy critters quick, but sometimes, all it'll do is build agro, kill wizzy, and then everyone else.<P>But with an added tank, there's someone else there taking hits for the rest of the group. In the case of epic pet, there's a 50 point DS on him if you're not too stupid to sick him in before he DS's himself. Use previous model to figure the dmg on that DS. <P>Mages have unlimited supply and availability to mod's ( which if you're not stupid, can actually help a mage in a solo situation ), and Focus items ( which if you think the're underpowered, or crap, you're just retarded ).<P>*sigh* this is tiring.<BR>If you think that because wizards are unbalanced because we nuke for more, you're just stupid because wizards are supposed to nuke for more. You're pointing out the obvious. Is a bard supposed to melee for more than a ranger, NO, because we're not rangers. Don't ***** about crit's for wizzy's because they make the nukes too powerfull. They're supposed to be powerfull, so they're right in line with the theme of what a wizard does.<P>VI has stated many times that ports do no a class ballance. It's more like a perk. Wizards are supposed to be the supreme casters, able to bend time and space around them to accomplish great things. That's the storyline around why wizards need runes for research...they're leftover artifacts from a great war fought by wizards. The point is wizards are supposed to do lot's of magical things...mages are supposed to summon things. Not summon things and do lot's of other neat magical things, just summon. You summon armor, arrows, mod's, stones, pets, food, bags, weapons, ( which, BTW, actually does affect your pet's stats. Equip a pet with full phantom plate, and it's defence is greatly increased ... well, maybe not greatly, but it's still increased. Point in case, Muzzle of Mardu. If item's didn't affect pets stats, why would a special ability work? )<P>Mages are a great utility class for the high end game, especially now with the summoned focus items. Yeah, rentable focus items will be implemented, but we don't know what they're gonna be about. Hell, a --== BETTER ==-- focus item may be something that gives 5% casttime improvement and stats...which would you rather have? 5% or 15 - 20%???<P>I'm getting off topic<P>Wizards are nukers...they nuke, and they're good at it. sometimes, a wizard bust's a vein and BOOM, crit blast.<P>Mages can crit blast, but they have to practice alot longer and harder than wizzy's...why? BECAUSE THEY'RE SUMMONERS, NOT BLASTERS!!!<P>Which, in character, is why mages have to wait for 55 and wizzy's have to wait for 11.<P>/bye<P>--------------------<P>..."Live to play, or get out of the way!!!"...
</FONT>
